{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Good afternoon."},{"time":1000,"text":"If you have followed"},{"time":3000,"text":"diplomatic news in the past weeks,"},{"time":5000,"text":"you may have heard of a kind of crisis"},{"time":7000,"text":"between China and the U.S."},{"time":9000,"text":"regarding cyberattacks"},{"time":11000,"text":"against the American company Google."},{"time":13000,"text":"Many things have been said about this."},{"time":15000,"text":"Some people have called a cyberwar"},{"time":17000,"text":"what may actually be"},{"time":19000,"text":"just a spy operation --"},{"time":21000,"text":"and obviously, a quite mishandled one."},{"time":23000,"text":"However, this episode reveals"},{"time":26000,"text":"the growing anxiety in the Western world"},{"time":28000,"text":"regarding these emerging cyber weapons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"It so happens that these weapons are dangerous."},{"time":33000,"text":"They're of a new nature:"},{"time":35000,"text":"they could lead the world"},{"time":37000,"text":"into a digital conflict"},{"time":39000,"text":"that could turn into an armed struggle."},{"time":41000,"text":"These virtual weapons can also destroy the physical world."},{"time":46000,"text":"In 1982, in the middle of the Cold War"},{"time":49000,"text":"in Soviet Siberia,"},{"time":51000,"text":"a pipeline exploded with a burst of 3 kilotons,"},{"time":55000,"text":"the equivalent of a fourth of the Hiroshima bomb."},{"time":57000,"text":"Now we know today -- this was revealed"},{"time":59000,"text":"by Thomas Reed,"},{"time":61000,"text":"Ronald Reagan's former U.S. Air Force Secretary --"},{"time":63000,"text":"this explosion was actually the result"},{"time":66000,"text":"of a CIA sabotage operation,"},{"time":68000,"text":"in which they had managed"},{"time":70000,"text":"to infiltrate the IT management systems"},{"time":72000,"text":"of that pipeline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"More recently, the U.S. government revealed"},{"time":77000,"text":"that in September 2008, more than 3 million people"},{"time":80000,"text":"in the state of Espirito Santo in Brazil"},{"time":83000,"text":"were plunged into darkness,"},{"time":85000,"text":"victims of a blackmail operation from cyber pirates."},{"time":90000,"text":"Even more worrying for the Americans,"},{"time":92000,"text":"in December 2008 the holiest of holies,"},{"time":95000,"text":"the IT systems of CENTCOM,"},{"time":97000,"text":"the central command"},{"time":99000,"text":"managing the wars in Iraq and Afghanistan,"},{"time":102000,"text":"may have been infiltrated by hackers"},{"time":104000,"text":"who used these:"},{"time":107000,"text":"plain but infected USB keys."},{"time":109000,"text":"And with these keys, they may have been able"},{"time":111000,"text":"to get inside CENTCOM's systems,"},{"time":113000,"text":"to see and hear everything,"},{"time":115000,"text":"and maybe even infect some of them."},{"time":117000,"text":"As a result, the Americans take the threat very seriously."},{"time":119000,"text":"I'll quote General James Cartwright,"},{"time":121000,"text":"Vice Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff,"},{"time":123000,"text":"who says in a report to Congress"},{"time":125000,"text":"that cyberattacks could be as powerful as"},{"time":128000,"text":"weapons of mass destruction."},{"time":131000,"text":"Moreover, the Americans have decided"},{"time":133000,"text":"to spend over 30 billion dollars"},{"time":135000,"text":"in the next five years"},{"time":136500,"text":"to build up their cyberwar capabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"And across the world today, we see"},{"time":141000,"text":"a sort of cyber arms race,"},{"time":144000,"text":"with cyberwar units"},{"time":146000,"text":"built up by countries like North Korea"},{"time":148000,"text":"or even Iran."},{"time":149000,"text":"Yet, what you'll never hear"},{"time":151000,"text":"from spokespeople"},{"time":153000,"text":"from the Pentagon or the French Department of Defence"},{"time":156000,"text":"is that the question isn't really"},{"time":158000,"text":"who's the enemy, but actually"},{"time":160000,"text":"the very nature of cyber weapons."},{"time":163000,"text":"And to understand why, we must look at how,"},{"time":165000,"text":"through the ages, military technologies"},{"time":168000,"text":"have maintained or destroyed"},{"time":170000,"text":"world peace."},{"time":173000,"text":"For example,"},{"time":175000,"text":"if we'd had TEDxParis"},{"time":176000,"text":"350 years ago,"},{"time":178000,"text":"we would have talked about the military innovation of the day --"},{"time":181000,"text":"the massive Vauban-style fortifications --"},{"time":184000,"text":"and we could have predicted"},{"time":186000,"text":"a period of stability in the world or in Europe."},{"time":189000,"text":"which was indeed the case in Europe"},{"time":192000,"text":"between 1650 and 1750."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"Similarly, if we'd had this talk"},{"time":197000,"text":"30 or 40 years ago, we would have seen"},{"time":200000,"text":"how the rise of nuclear weapons,"},{"time":202000,"text":"and the threat of mutually assured destruction they imply,"},{"time":206000,"text":"prevents a direct fight between the two superpowers."},{"time":210000,"text":"However, if we'd had this talk 60 years ago,"},{"time":212000,"text":"we would have seen how the emergence"},{"time":215000,"text":"of new aircraft and tank technologies,"},{"time":218000,"text":"which give the advantage to the attacker,"},{"time":221000,"text":"make the Blitzkrieg doctrine very credible"},{"time":224000,"text":"and thus create the possibility of war in Europe."},{"time":227000,"text":"So military technologies"},{"time":229000,"text":"can influence the course of the world,"},{"time":231000,"text":"can make or break world peace --"},{"time":233000,"text":"and there lies the issue with cyber weapons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"The first issue:"},{"time":237000,"text":"Imagine a potential enemy announcing"},{"time":240000,"text":"they're building a cyberwar unit,"},{"time":242000,"text":"but only for their country's defense."},{"time":244000,"text":"Okay, but what distinguishes it"},{"time":247000,"text":"from an offensive unit?"},{"time":249000,"text":"It gets even more complicated"},{"time":251000,"text":"when the doctrines of use become ambiguous."},{"time":255000,"text":"Just 3 years ago, both the U.S. and France"},{"time":259000,"text":"were saying they were investing militarily in cyberspace,"},{"time":263000,"text":"strictly to defend their IT systems."},{"time":266000,"text":"But today both countries say"},{"time":269000,"text":"the best defense is to attack."},{"time":271000,"text":"And so, they're joining China,"},{"time":273000,"text":"whose doctrine of use for 15 years has been"},{"time":277000,"text":"both defensive and offensive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"The second issue:"},{"time":282000,"text":"Your country could be under cyberattack"},{"time":286000,"text":"with entire regions plunged into total darkness,"},{"time":289000,"text":"and you may not even know"},{"time":291000,"text":"who's attacking you."},{"time":293000,"text":"Cyber weapons have this peculiar feature:"},{"time":294800,"text":"they can be used"},{"time":296300,"text":"without leaving traces."},{"time":298000,"text":"This gives a tremendous advantage to the attacker,"},{"time":300000,"text":"because the defender"},{"time":302000,"text":"doesn't know who to fight back against."},{"time":304000,"text":"And if the defender retaliates against the wrong adversary,"},{"time":306000,"text":"they risk making one more enemy"},{"time":309000,"text":"and ending up diplomatically isolated."},{"time":311000,"text":"This issue isn't just theoretical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"In May 2007, Estonia was the victim of cyberattacks,"},{"time":315000,"text":"that damaged its communication"},{"time":318000,"text":"and banking systems."},{"time":320000,"text":"Estonia accused Russia."},{"time":322000,"text":"But NATO, though it defends Estonia,"},{"time":324000,"text":"reacted very prudently. Why?"},{"time":326000,"text":"Because NATO couldn't be 100% sure"},{"time":328000,"text":"that the Kremlin was indeed behind these attacks."},{"time":333000,"text":"So to sum up, on the one hand,"},{"time":336000,"text":"when a possible enemy announces"},{"time":338000,"text":"they're building a cyberwar unit,"},{"time":340000,"text":"you don't know whether it's for attack"},{"time":342000,"text":"or defense."},{"time":343000,"text":"On the other hand,"},{"time":344000,"text":"we know that these weapons give an advantage to attacking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"In a major article published in 1978,"},{"time":351000,"text":"Professor Robert Jervis of Columbia University in New York"},{"time":353000,"text":"described a model to understand"},{"time":355000,"text":"how conflicts could arise."},{"time":357000,"text":"In this context,"},{"time":360000,"text":"when you don't know if the potential enemy"},{"time":362000,"text":"is preparing for defense or attack,"},{"time":365000,"text":"and if the weapons give an advantage to attacking,"},{"time":367000,"text":"then this environment is"},{"time":369000,"text":"most likely to spark a conflict."},{"time":373000,"text":"This is the environment that's being created"},{"time":375000,"text":"by cyber weapons today,"},{"time":377000,"text":"and historically it was the environment in Europe"},{"time":380000,"text":"at the onset of World War I."},{"time":384000,"text":"So cyber weapons"},{"time":386000,"text":"are dangerous by nature,"},{"time":388000,"text":"but in addition, they're emerging"},{"time":391000,"text":"in a much more unstable environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393000,"text":"If you remember the Cold War,"},{"time":395000,"text":"it was a very hard game,"},{"time":397000,"text":"but a stable one played only by two players,"},{"time":399000,"text":"which allowed for some coordination between the two superpowers."},{"time":402000,"text":"Today we're moving to a multipolar world"},{"time":407000,"text":"in which coordination is much more complicated,"},{"time":408000,"text":"as we have seen at Copenhagen."},{"time":411000,"text":"And this coordination may become even trickier"},{"time":414000,"text":"with the introduction of cyber weapons."},{"time":417000,"text":"Why? Because no nation"},{"time":419000,"text":"knows for sure whether its neighbor"},{"time":422000,"text":"is about to attack."},{"time":424000,"text":"So nations may live under the threat"},{"time":426000,"text":"of what Nobel Prize winner Thomas Schelling"},{"time":429000,"text":"called the \"reciprocal fear of surprise attack,\""},{"time":431000,"text":"as I don't know if my neighbor"},{"time":433000,"text":"is about to attack me or not --"},{"time":435000,"text":"I may never know --"},{"time":437000,"text":"so I might take the upper hand"},{"time":439000,"text":"and attack first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"Just last week,"},{"time":444000,"text":"in a New York Times article dated January 26, 2010,"},{"time":448000,"text":"it was revealed for the first time that"},{"time":450000,"text":"officials at the National Security Agency"},{"time":453000,"text":"were considering the possibility of preemptive attacks"},{"time":457000,"text":"in cases where the U.S. was about"},{"time":460000,"text":"to be cyberattacked."},{"time":463000,"text":"And these preemptive attacks"},{"time":465000,"text":"might not just remain"},{"time":466000,"text":"in cyberspace."},{"time":470000,"text":"In May 2009, General Kevin Chilton,"},{"time":475000,"text":"commander of the U.S. nuclear forces,"},{"time":478000,"text":"stated that in the event of cyberattacks against the U.S.,"},{"time":483000,"text":"all options would be on the table."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"Cyber weapons do not replace"},{"time":488000,"text":"conventional or nuclear weapons --"},{"time":490000,"text":"they just add a new layer to the existing system of terror."},{"time":495000,"text":"But in doing so, they also add their own risk"},{"time":498000,"text":"of triggering a conflict --"},{"time":500000,"text":"as we've just seen, a very important risk --"},{"time":502000,"text":"and a risk we may have to confront"},{"time":504000,"text":"with a collective security solution"},{"time":507000,"text":"which includes all of us:"},{"time":509000,"text":"European allies, NATO members,"},{"time":511000,"text":"our American friends and allies,"},{"time":513000,"text":"our other Western allies,"},{"time":515000,"text":"and maybe, by forcing their hand a little,"},{"time":517000,"text":"our Russian and Chinese partners."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"The information technologies"},{"time":522000,"text":"Joël de Rosnay was talking about,"},{"time":523500,"text":"which were historically born from military research,"},{"time":526000,"text":"are today on the verge of developing"},{"time":528000,"text":"an offensive capability of destruction,"},{"time":531000,"text":"which could tomorrow, if we're not careful,"},{"time":535000,"text":"completely destroy world peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}